### Punctuation

1. **Never use the em dash `â€”`** (U+2014) in ship-log copy.
2. Prefer comma, colon, or period for clause breaks.

### On-image discipline

Same char limits as below. Punchy headlines; shorter beats restyling. Align photo card thesis with video statement and X thesis paste (same story, length tuned per surface).

## Photo cards (1200Ă—675)

1. **Only change copy in content files** â€” `*Photo.ts`, `*Update.ts`, `shareCopies/*`. Do not edit layout CSS or template components unless fixing a systemic export bug.

2. **Respect export-safe character limits** â€” validated at import by `validatePhotoPostContent.ts` via `definePhotoUpdate()`:
   - `title` â‰¤ 36 chars (cover lockup titles â€” keep short, e.g. `PayAI Ă— Syra`)
   - `headline` â‰¤ 64 chars
   - `subtitle` / `body` / `narrative` â‰¤ 180â€“240 chars (see `POST_PHOTO_FIELD_LIMITS`)
   - `badge` â‰¤ 42 chars
   - List items (highlights, steps, cards, stats) have per-item limits â€” check the validator

3. **Do not change `layout` on existing cards** unless explicitly asked. Each of the 15 cards has a fixed role â†’ layout mapping in `photoCardSlots.ts`.

4. **Prefer shorter copy over smaller CSS** â€” if text overflows in preview, shorten the string; do not shrink fonts or remove spacing.

5. **Cover spotlight (`photo-cover-spotlight`)** â€” blocks: eyebrow, badge, logo-lockup (logo + title), subtitle. Title sits beside the logo; long titles wrap and break PNG export. Keep titles under ~28 chars and subtitles under ~160 chars.

6. **After content edits**, run `npm run test -- validateAllPhotoPosts` â€” validates all ship-log photo decks (including the locked Format Template).

7. **Export architecture** â€” PNG copy/download captures `PostPhotoExportStage` (off-screen 1200Ă—675), not the scaled preview frame. Export-safe CSS lives on `.post-photo-export-root` and applies to every ship log automatically. Never point export refs at CSS-scaled preview nodes.

## Video slides (960Ă—540 â†’ 1080p export)

1. Same copy discipline â€” shorter beats restyling.
2. Video export uses `PostVideoExportStage` off-screen; do not capture the scaled preview stage.
3. New updates must use `defineVideoUpdate()` (8 kinds). Unique layouts per slide when possible (`validatePostUpdate` warns on duplicates in dev).
4. Reference the locked Format Template at `/post/video/0` and `/post/photo/0`.

## Verification checklist

Before marking a post content task done:

- [ ] Preview card/slide readable at default zoom
- [ ] Download PNG (photo) or WebM (video) matches preview â€” no overlapping title/body
- [ ] No validation errors from `definePhotoUpdate` / `defineVideoUpdate`
- [ ] Share copy files updated alongside card content when applicable
- [ ] No em dash `â€”` in any ship-log copy string
- [ ] Each of the 15 photo shareCopies is a distinct angle (see role map)
- [ ] `shareCopyVideo` ends with video CTA; photo shares end with product CTA when relevant

## What breaks exports (avoid)

- `text-wrap: balance` on long multi-line titles (handled in CSS for capture, but still avoid very long titles)
- Capturing nodes inside `transform: scale(...)` wrappers
- Adding blocks to a layout registry entry without checking the template supports them
- Exceeding field limits in `POST_PHOTO_FIELD_LIMITS`
- Deviating from the 8-slide / 15-card slot contract for new ship logs
